#: ../../Rapid_Mix/RM_Intro.rst:17
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"“In summary, little is known about rapid mix, much less any sensitivity to "
"scale. However, the models and data reviewed suggest the need to be on the "
"lookout for certain effects. From what is presently known, it can be speculated "
"that since coagulant precipitation is sensitive to both micro- and macro-"
"mixing, scale-up must consider not only energy dissipation rate, but also the "
"reaction injection point and the contacting method.” - `Mixing in Coagulation "
"and Flocculation 1991 page 292 <https://books.google.com/books/about/"
"Mixing_in_coagulation_and_flocculation.html?id=dkFSAAAAMAAJ>`_."
